ID: Ch11b-Buy
TEXT: 

 "Guys," I say, "I think I may have a plan."
"What the hell?" Daren says. "What's with the crazy magical energy radiating from you all of a sudden? Don't tell me that Eiden froze time again to give you magic powers!"

"No," I say, as I start to reinforce the magical barrier. "It wasn't Eiden. I just used my device to harness the energy that's being leaked from the stillwaters."

"You can do that now?" Daren asks me.

"Apparently," I say.

"So what's this plan of yours, then?" Daren asks.

"Well," I say, "remember how Azarius told us last time that the necromancer's spell only lasts five minutes and that it can only be cast once a day? I was thinking that we could just wait them out, while we keep reinforcing the barrier and attacking them from a distance."

"In that case, I'm hoping that you have some really good reinforcement spells," Daren says, "because I've pretty much already exhausted all of mine."

"Don't worry," I say. "You just focus on keeping the barrier up. I'll take care of the reinforcements."

I turn towards Flower and Kate.

"Can you three put some pressure on the stillwaters while Daren and I keep the barrier up?" I say.

"Aye, aye, sir!" Flower says, as she performs a military salute with her right hand.

 "I'll see what I can do," Kate says.
"Try to aim for the skeleton maintaining their magical barrier as much as possible," I say. "He's the one that's going to be busy undoing my reinforcement spells."

"And what am I supposed to do all this time?" Hadrik asks.

"Well, you can, uh..." I start to say, but I pause to think for a second. "You can be our last line of defense and make sure to punch back all of their spells in case our barrier fails before the time limit."

"Great!" Hadrik says. "It's times like these that make me regret the fact that I didn't bring a pack of playing cards with me when I joined the tournament."

Once everyone agrees to follow my plan, I go back to reinforcing Daren's barrier, while Kate, Flower and Illuna start to cast their spells at the stillwaters. Holding the barrier against so many simultaneous attacks is proving to be a little more difficult than I had originally thought. Daren is already at his limit, and keeping the barrier up by myself is quickly starting to drain me of energy. The girls don't seem to be doing very well either, because they've yet to break through the skeletons' barrier, while the supporting stillwater is doing all he can to counter my reinforcement spells.

This isn't working out. I need to revise my plan, or we're not going to last until the five minute mark.

